{
  "texts": [
    "For addressing this issue, a voting scheme has been applied to cover each non-empty voxel, resulting in complexity of computations that was analogous to the number of occupied voxels.",
    "Additionally, other methods have been developed towards saving memory and accelerating computation by fully utilizing the sparsity of voxels.",
    "Point-based methods use directly raw point clouds as inputs.",
    "While these methods can be timeconsuming, they can be mitigated using fusion sampling strategies [193].",
    "While saliency perception could aid segmentation, localization and detection tasks, it should be noted that relevant research on 3D point clouds is limited."
  ]
}